\f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 I\rquote d worked on a problem called - well, it was to do with the strength of spot-welded joints.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 
Spot-welded joints are such that bits, that are, say, ten things holding something together, and when they\rquote re put under a load, one or two of them can break, but the rest of t
hem may be strong enough to hold the structure. And there are some probability problems connected with that, which I solved in a very cumbersome and complicated way.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 And I was in the library \endash 
 Farnborough had a rather good library - and I was in the library reading the Proceedings of the Royal Society, and I came across a paper called something like, \'93The Strengths of Bundles of Threads\'94
, and it suddenly dawned on me that this was the same problem that I\rquote d solved, but this man, Henry Daniels (?? \endash  7.40) he was called, had given a beautiful solution.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 Mine was horrible, but it was a solution.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 And as I went out of the library, there was an advertisement \endash 
 the War had ended, and we were not constrained, and the normal thing, I was going back to Cambridge to do the third year. [The advertisement was for] a post to work with Dr. H. E. (?? \endash  8.05) Daniels, at the Wool Industry\rquote 
s Research Association, Leeds.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 The same man.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 
And I was so taken with this paper that I applied for this job. Henry -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 that\rquote s the man there \endash  he told me years later, I was the only applicant!}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 But I\rquote m not quite sure whether that he was implying I only got the job because I was the only \'85 (LAUGHS)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 
But then, so instead of going back to Cambridge, I went up to Leeds, and worked at this place called \'93The Wool Industries Research Association\'94. And that was the best decision, scientifically, I\rquote ve ever made \endash 
 not going back to Cambridge, I should say. Because the system in those days, many industries had these Research Associations which were half-funded by the State, and half by a levy on the industry, so there was a lot of freedom.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
