I mean, a lot of the work was commissioned by the industry, but a lot of it wasn\rquote t. For example, the man who developed what\rquote s called \'93chromatography\'94, which is a method for se
parating complex [mixtures of] molecules and their components, he worked there, and he\rquote d just won the Nobel Prize for Chemistry.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 So there was a Nobel Prize winner, there was Henry Daniels who was absolutely brilliant, and there were other unknown but very 
