\par David:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 Well statistics in science is concerned with the design of investigations and the analysis of data, where there\rquote 
s substantial unexplained variability.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 
Random error, haphazard variation between [material], people [and so on]. It\rquote s the methods that are used for handling such data of that kind, and for its careful interpretation.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 It\rquote s
, in that sense, quite different from official statistics which, in the UK particularly, is essentially concerned with counting people accurately.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 There\rquote s this tradition, particularly strong in British official statistics - much less so in Swedish and Cana
dian statistics - where they collect data and analyse it, interpret it, but here you don\rquote t interpret the data. You collect the numbers, and you say, \'93We\rquote re assured that these numbers are more or less right in some sense or another.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 They may or may not be helpful, that\rquote 
s up to you.\'94 That\rquote s the official statistics line, which is changing, of course, it\rquote s more subtle than I\rquote m explaining it, but that\rquote 
s a very different ethos from statistics in science, which is trying to help in the design of experiments and design of sample surveys and other investigations, and in [asking], \'93
What are you reasonably entitled to conclude from these data, about the research questions that you had in mind when you collected the data?\'94}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 So it\rquote s the formal side and the theory of the formal side, the nature of probability. How does probability help you do these things?}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15738878\charrsid15738878 That\rquote s the side that I\rquote 
ve almost exclusively worked on.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16597392 
